## Testing plan

- `build` gate: `dotnet build Berreman.slnx -c Release` from `Berreman/` MUST pass with the new Domain/Storage/Ui modules compiling in one pass; `MaterialPreview.fs` builds against the public MIT Avalonia.FuncUI NuGet (NOT the clone).
- `unit-tests` gate: `dotnet test --no-build -c Release` from `Berreman/BerremanTests/` stays green (this slice does not touch `BerremanTests`).
- `constructor-unit-tests` gate runs the new `OpticalConstructor.Tests` files (all hosted in `OpticalConstructor.Tests`, reconciler round-2 §g) and MUST increase the count over slice 003's baseline:
  - `DispersionModelsTests.fs` — `evaluate` reproduces `Silicon`/`Langasite` closures and uniaxial maps to `Eps.fromComplexRefractionIndex (n_o,n_e,n_o)` (AC-D4/AC-D5); `Some thermoOptic` applies first-order `dndT·(T−referenceTemperature)` and `None` is byte-identical to the isothermal index, only `dndT`/`referenceTemperature` persisted (AC-D8); `resolveMaterial lib id λ` returns the concrete `OpticalProperties` for a known `materialEntry` id at the supplied `WaveLength` and `Result.Error (UnknownMaterialId _)` for an unknown id (the by-id resolution seam slices 005/014 delegate to).
  - `MaterialImportTests.fs` — fixture refractiveindex.info µm YAML and a nm CSV import to entries whose `getEps` matches expected n,k after meter reduction (AC-D3), using `fixtures/Si.yml` and `fixtures/sample-nk.csv`.
- AC-D7 (spectral-unit toggle): the eV-toggled preview passes `plotN11` the same canonical-meter `Range<WaveLength>` as the nm toggle — only axis labels/scale differ, no re-storage of non-SI units. Exercised at the `MaterialPreview.fs` chart boundary (the underlying `wavelengthToUnit` conversion is already proven in slice 002's `UnitsTests`).

## Risks

- **Medium.** The dispersion catalogue must reproduce the engine's hand-built `Silicon`/`Langasite` closures bit-for-bit (within 1e-9), and the `materialEntry` `$def` must fill cleanly into the slice-003 envelope. The thermo-optic path is the easiest to get wrong: `None` MUST be byte-identical to the isothermal result (no closure overhead), `Some` MUST apply exactly `dndT·(T−referenceTemperature)`, and the operating temperature `T` MUST NOT be persisted while `dndT`/`referenceTemperature` round-trip in SI 1/K and K. The net-new `[<Measure>] K` MUST live in `DispersionModels.fs` and MUST NOT shadow `Constants.fs`. Mitigation: prove `evaluate`/uniaxial/thermo-optic by unit test against the engine presets before exit; keep all conversion arithmetic routed through `Units.fs` (no literal factors) per §D.11.

## Hand-off

The materials half of Part D exists and is unit-tested: the dispersion-model coefficient catalogue and `evaluate`/`toOpticalProperties` (`DispersionModels.fs`), the anisotropic three-index path, the optional `ThermoOptic` dn/dT + net-new `[<Measure>] K`, the searchable `MaterialLibrary` with built-in `Silicon`/`Langasite`/`Standard` presets plus the by-id `resolveMaterial` resolution seam (`MaterialLibrary.fs`) that slice 005 (§B.6 medium selectors) and slice 014 (§J.4 drag-drop) delegate to, refractiveindex.info YAML / CSV import and CSV export (`MaterialImport.fs`), and the spectral-preview routing into `Analytics/Charting.fs` with a nm/µm/Å/eV/cm⁻¹ toggle (`MaterialPreview.fs`). The `materialEntry` `$def` dispersion sub-object is filled in the schema. Later slices: slice 005 (Part B) adds the stack editor and crystal-axis rotation; slice 013 (Part I §I.8) adds the shareable material-library file format and material import/export over the storage seam. Emit the state-of-the-world file with all required ATX headings (`Where we are`, `What's working`, `Tests`, `Architecture`, `Deferred`, `Gotchas`, `Changelog`) and a fenced `gates:` YAML baseline block carrying the updated `constructor-unit-tests` count so the next slice's `count_at_least` gate has a baseline.
